snippet.title: Folding a Circle into an Ellipse
snippet.description:
Here's a fun activity for you to try. Starting with a circular sheet of paper and a point marked on the inside, I'll show you how to draw lines to reveal an ellipse that has the marked point and the center of the circle as its foci (and explain why this works).

Twitter: @TPointMath


Music:

"Fretless" Kevin MacLeod (incompetech.com)
